$1 $2 ...$N args passed to script $@
$@ vs $*
$@ treats args seperately
$* treats as single args

all variables passed to script : $#
script name :$0
present which direcrory you are in : $PWD 
who is running this script : $USER 
Home directory of the user: $HOME
PID of script: $$
sleep 100 &
Background proccess id: $!
number of vars passed to script: $#


